						<div class="postbody">I have been looking for some basic board at work for building an IOT related test terminal for one of our project. While seaching for possible boards I ended up on the Raspberry PI and the Arduino.<br /><br />When I saw the Arduino, the first thing that came to my mind was &quot;hey, there may be some interesting stuff that can be done with that, maybe even nes related&quot;.  Since I always wanted to learn more about electronic I thought that it could be a starting point.<br /><br />At first I would just experiment with it but what I would like to know if it could be used in any kind of nes related project and what kind of project? What are the limitation of such mico-controllers?</div>

