						<div class="postbody">If you need some project idea for an Arduino, you could try and build either a wireless Controller, or a Controller to USB adapter.<br />I am currently on building the first; a wireless SNES Controller, with Mouse support using a laser mouse (I found a PS/2 Mouse that uses a laser for movement detection) and PC transfer support. I needed a method to transfer porgrams (and data) from my PC to my SNES (of course with a supporting bootloader), so I figured why not going for the whole package when I need to chop up a controller anyways. Using the Attiny series, which is supported by the Arduino IDE, this can be done pretty much in a compact form-factor (Digispark for example are very cheap, like 1$ for a board, and they offer USB capabilities, like keyboard and joystick emulation, in a very small form-factor).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

