						<div class="postbody">Raspberry Pis run at 3V; many 5V PROMS disallow programming when they're supplied that low of a voltage.<br /><br />I think I remember people saying that the Raspberry Pi GPIO speed is disappointingly slow, too ... so much so that it might be faster to have the raspberry pi talk to the arduino rather than toggle its own pins.<br /><br />(Specific exceptions for SPI, IÂ²C, or IÂ²S peripherals)</div>

