						<div class="postbody">GPIOs on the Raspberry Pi are fast when you mmap the /dev/mem file and write to the correct offsets. This is also a very questionable practice. Better would be to make a kernel module, implement the desired GPIO protocol and communicate to ordinary userspace processes using only &quot;high-level&quot; messages (instead of controlling every pin from userspace, ask the driver to do a certain job)</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />((Î» (x) (x x)) (Î» (x) (x x)))</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

